    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So you're saying procedural due process is basically just about the \"surface-level\" rules, while substantive due process is what actually gets to the heart of justice? That's a pretty strong way to frame it. If a student argued that the \"substantive\" approach is actually dangerous because it lets unelected judges basically make up new rights that aren't explicitly in the Constitution, how would you respond to that?",
